WEBVTT

00:06.006 --> 00:08.007
♪ ♪

00:10.051 --> 00:12.679
[zapping]

00:15.099 --> 00:17.643
Keyleth, wake up.

00:19.978 --> 00:22.189
Keyleth! No.

00:26.652 --> 00:29.196
An elixir. Try this.

00:29.280 --> 00:31.114
Quickly.

00:35.536 --> 00:37.704
VAX:
It's not working.

00:37.787 --> 00:39.999
We're losing her!

00:40.082 --> 00:42.084
The Whispered One
did not return.

00:42.167 --> 00:44.837
We failed.
It was too soon.

00:44.920 --> 00:46.463
There's nothing to be done.

00:46.546 --> 00:48.466
Keyleth is gone.

00:48.548 --> 00:50.593
But at least we have
what we came for.

00:52.427 --> 00:53.887
The fuck are you talking about?!

00:53.970 --> 00:56.182
Keyleth is still breathing.

00:56.265 --> 01:00.268
Something's not right.
Uh, let me try, uh...

01:00.351 --> 01:02.604
♪ Scanlan's hand ♪♪

01:02.688 --> 01:05.566
The elixir, my spell--

01:05.649 --> 01:07.567
that thing must be
blocking all magic.

01:07.650 --> 01:09.986
Damn it, he's right.
Away from the orb!

01:10.069 --> 01:11.822
We're not done with you yet.

01:11.906 --> 01:14.450
[grunting]

01:21.706 --> 01:23.250
Hmm?

01:25.878 --> 01:28.923
Finders keepers.

01:29.006 --> 01:31.966
W-Whoa.

01:32.051 --> 01:34.719
Hey! Let's move, big guy!

01:36.764 --> 01:38.765
[grunts]

01:38.848 --> 01:40.600
- [panting]
- [Grog] Hey.

01:41.644 --> 01:43.978
Easy, I got her from here.

01:44.063 --> 01:45.939
Thank you, Grog.

01:53.739 --> 01:55.865
Okay, wait-wait-wait,
hold up, hold up.

01:55.950 --> 01:57.033
♪ Scanlan's hand ♪♪

01:57.116 --> 01:58.117
Yes!

01:58.201 --> 02:00.328
We got magic.

02:00.412 --> 02:02.706
Vex, another elixir!

02:05.209 --> 02:06.376
I need it, hurry!

02:07.837 --> 02:11.423
[sighs] There's just,
there's no more.

02:15.635 --> 02:18.889
- Keyleth...
- [whimpers]

02:21.891 --> 02:23.936
Forgive me.

02:26.396 --> 02:28.399
♪ ♪

02:31.860 --> 02:35.322
- [crying]
- Brother.

02:35.406 --> 02:37.365
I'm so sorry.

02:47.293 --> 02:50.211
Wait. Herbs...

02:50.295 --> 02:52.256
What else did she use?

02:52.338 --> 02:55.050
Shorthalt! Need that magic!

02:57.468 --> 02:58.637
Uh...

02:58.721 --> 03:00.472
♪ Disgusting mud and spit ♪

03:00.556 --> 03:03.224
♪ Turn into some healing shit ♪♪

03:06.020 --> 03:09.439
Come on, work. Work.

03:12.526 --> 03:14.903
- [grunts]
- You controlled me for years.

03:14.986 --> 03:17.114
Now it's your turn to suffer.

03:17.197 --> 03:20.700
What was the ritual meant to do?
Answer me!

03:22.118 --> 03:25.038
I only answer to
the Whispered One.

03:25.122 --> 03:30.085
But he denied me.
Abandoned me.

03:30.169 --> 03:32.629
[Percy] I'll gladly
send you to him.

03:32.712 --> 03:34.298
Go ahead.

03:34.381 --> 03:38.551
You've taken my husband and
any hope of getting him back.

03:38.635 --> 03:41.847
What more could I lose?

03:41.930 --> 03:44.349
End me.

03:45.808 --> 03:48.437
No. Your pain will linger.

03:48.520 --> 03:51.481
I'll shatter your ankles
for my sister Vesper.

03:51.564 --> 03:53.901
Your hands belong to Julius.

03:53.984 --> 03:56.361
Each de Rolo will have
their pound of flesh,

03:56.444 --> 03:59.031
until I flay the skin
from what's left of you.

03:59.114 --> 04:00.699
Oh, okay, Percy,

04:00.782 --> 04:02.158
taking this a little far.

04:02.241 --> 04:04.036
Hey, why don't you
just lower the...

04:04.118 --> 04:06.663
[grunting]

04:06.747 --> 04:08.164
The fuck?

04:08.247 --> 04:10.209
[Percy] Your suffering
will be merely a taste

04:10.292 --> 04:13.294
of the pain you inflicted
upon my family.

04:13.378 --> 04:15.004
[laughs]

04:15.088 --> 04:17.882
[Cassandra] The smoke.
It's even worse.

04:17.966 --> 04:20.259
[Vex] It's some sort of curse.

04:20.343 --> 04:22.428
Pike felt something
clouding his soul.

04:22.512 --> 04:24.555
I thought she meant
he was just depressed.

04:24.639 --> 04:26.684
Something has possession of you.

04:26.766 --> 04:29.228
[Orthax] And we are
better for it.

04:29.310 --> 04:31.187
We? What?

04:31.271 --> 04:32.689
Percy!

04:32.773 --> 04:34.983
[Keyleth] That's not Percy.

04:35.067 --> 04:36.360
Keyleth?

04:36.442 --> 04:39.737
It's a demon. Look.

04:40.781 --> 04:43.117
- [roars]
- [Vex] Holy shit.

04:43.199 --> 04:45.451
How?

04:45.536 --> 04:47.745
If it gets what it wants,

04:47.829 --> 04:51.125
I don't think much of Percy
will be left.

04:51.207 --> 04:53.377
Vex'ahlia, what are you doing?

04:58.298 --> 05:00.634
Step aside.

05:00.718 --> 05:03.302
You're going to shoot me, too?

05:03.387 --> 05:06.223
[overlapping voices] If we must.

05:06.305 --> 05:09.935
I know you're in there.

05:10.019 --> 05:13.605
Darling, take off the mask.

05:20.153 --> 05:22.113
[whimpering]

05:24.158 --> 05:25.617
[Vex] It's all right.

05:25.701 --> 05:27.244
You can put it down.

05:27.326 --> 05:30.956
It... it won't let me.

05:36.252 --> 05:38.755
- Don't do it!
- Percy. You can't!

05:38.838 --> 05:41.425
I don't know what else to do!

05:41.507 --> 05:43.927
[Orthax] No!

05:44.011 --> 05:45.428
No!

05:45.512 --> 05:47.680
[screaming]

05:50.683 --> 05:52.519
[roaring]

05:52.603 --> 05:54.228
Nope. Do not like.

05:54.312 --> 05:55.271
Everyone get back.

05:55.355 --> 05:57.356
[grunting]

06:00.026 --> 06:01.569
- Sister!
- Don't hurt him.

06:01.653 --> 06:02.904
He's not in control.

06:02.987 --> 06:04.531
Fuck that, he's got Vex.

06:04.615 --> 06:06.199
That thing can't bleed,

06:06.283 --> 06:09.286
but Percy can.
If it's inside his mind,

06:09.369 --> 06:13.040
his soul, only he can stop it.

06:13.122 --> 06:17.668
We'll buy time then. Oi,
keep him from killing Delilah!

06:17.752 --> 06:18.670
Piece of cake.

06:18.754 --> 06:20.004
♪ Scanlan's hand! ♪

06:23.966 --> 06:26.345
[Percy] She belongs to me!

06:29.889 --> 06:33.101
♪ ♪

06:33.185 --> 06:35.437
[Orthax] Shall I take over?

06:35.521 --> 06:37.064
[grunting]

06:37.146 --> 06:38.439
[Percy] No. No!

06:38.524 --> 06:41.776
[Orthax] I'm afraid I must.

06:41.860 --> 06:43.862
- Percy!
- [screaming]

06:49.033 --> 06:51.911
[grunting softly]

06:54.497 --> 06:58.334
[indistinct voices echoing]

06:58.418 --> 07:00.629
[sinister laughter]

07:00.711 --> 07:02.004
[voices continue indistinctly]

07:02.088 --> 07:04.507
Pay attention, children.
Today's lesson

07:04.591 --> 07:07.427
is on the subject of vengeance.

07:10.305 --> 07:13.975
Which is more powerful,
the desire for revenge

07:14.059 --> 07:17.228
or the ability to forgive?

07:17.312 --> 07:18.855
Care to demonstrate?

07:22.608 --> 07:24.569
[Cassandra whimpers]

07:24.653 --> 07:26.279
[laughs]

07:26.362 --> 07:27.822
Bastards!

07:29.699 --> 07:31.951
- [sizzling]
- Top marks, Percival.

07:32.034 --> 07:34.704
I'll kill you.

07:34.788 --> 07:35.831
I'll kill you all!

07:40.043 --> 07:43.754
[grunts] Goody.
Now I get to use my new toy.

07:43.838 --> 07:45.340
Wait, Grog! You can't.

07:45.423 --> 07:48.218
I was only gonna chop him
a little.

07:48.302 --> 07:49.927
Let her go!

07:50.012 --> 07:52.305
- Cassandra!
- [yelps]

07:53.682 --> 07:55.391
- Cassandra!
- [laughs]

07:55.475 --> 07:57.476
[panting, grunting]

08:00.814 --> 08:01.939
[laughter echoes]

08:02.024 --> 08:06.653
[laughs] What's the matter, son?
Not hungry?

08:06.737 --> 08:10.072
You look pale, boy.
Like you've seen a ghost.

08:12.117 --> 08:13.660
[door opens]

08:13.744 --> 08:15.286
- [laughter]
- [gasps]

08:15.370 --> 08:17.163
Death to the de Rolos.

08:17.247 --> 08:19.875
Stop. Not again.

08:19.957 --> 08:22.793
Not again!
I won't let you take them!

08:25.880 --> 08:27.966
So we just wait for him
to kill us?

08:30.177 --> 08:32.053
He has to reload eventually.

08:32.136 --> 08:34.431
Right?

08:37.768 --> 08:39.101
[Orthax] The hate.

08:40.937 --> 08:42.272
Embrace it.

08:43.981 --> 08:45.524
Or else...

08:45.609 --> 08:46.692
[breath quivering]

08:50.322 --> 08:53.158
You have failed us, son!

08:53.241 --> 08:54.784
[Lord de Rolo] A family
slaughtered,

08:54.868 --> 08:56.536
a legacy lost.

08:56.620 --> 08:58.996
You must avenge us!

08:59.081 --> 09:02.333
Please, son, you must!

09:02.417 --> 09:04.253
[whimpers] I'm sorry, Mother!

09:12.052 --> 09:14.513
Fuck, that burns.

09:14.596 --> 09:17.265
Listen to us!
You must fight this!

09:17.349 --> 09:18.808
[roars]

09:18.892 --> 09:21.727
Fight. Yes.

09:27.942 --> 09:33.657
Yes. One well-placed shot
and the pain disappears.

09:36.326 --> 09:38.245
[Vex] Fight it!

09:38.327 --> 09:39.578
Vex?

09:39.663 --> 09:42.124
Wait. No.

09:42.206 --> 09:44.084
- What are you doing to me?
- [sinister laughter]

09:44.167 --> 09:47.754
Giving you what you wanted,
Percival.

09:47.837 --> 09:49.338
Who are you?!

09:49.423 --> 09:53.009
You know exactly who I am.

09:53.092 --> 09:56.096
You summoned me. [screeches]

09:56.888 --> 10:00.225
Your torment
and thirst for revenge

10:00.308 --> 10:02.601
called me to your side.

10:02.686 --> 10:07.149
An unspoken partnership.

10:07.231 --> 10:11.445
Deep down, you remember.

10:11.528 --> 10:13.697
Welcoming my help.

10:13.779 --> 10:18.994
Welcoming the rage
that fueled you to create it.

10:19.076 --> 10:22.456
The weapon.

10:22.538 --> 10:24.832
[Percy] What are you
talking about?

10:24.916 --> 10:27.668
[Orthax] Forged in iron
and smoke.

10:29.046 --> 10:32.298
We struck a bargain.

10:32.381 --> 10:35.885
I gave you the means
for revenge.

10:35.969 --> 10:37.346
And you...

10:37.428 --> 10:41.892
gave me souls to feast upon.

10:41.975 --> 10:44.019
[screeches]

10:47.105 --> 10:50.609
Liar! [growls]

10:52.152 --> 10:55.404
You're not under a charm
anymore, damn it. Do something!

10:55.489 --> 10:57.865
Against a demon? What?

10:57.948 --> 11:00.369
You're his sister. Reach him.

11:00.451 --> 11:02.913
♪ ♪

11:02.995 --> 11:04.538
Percival!

11:04.623 --> 11:06.792
I know you.

11:06.875 --> 11:09.043
This isn't who you are!

11:09.126 --> 11:10.921
It's who I want to be.

11:11.004 --> 11:13.255
Yes, hate feels good.

11:13.340 --> 11:15.049
It drowns the pain.

11:15.133 --> 11:18.177
I've seen how easily
it consumes you.

11:19.721 --> 11:21.556
It's all I have left.

11:24.643 --> 11:28.730
If you reclaim yourself, you
won't hurt the ones you love.

11:28.813 --> 11:31.566
Find the real Percy within.

11:31.649 --> 11:33.442
Find my brother.

11:33.527 --> 11:35.570
Cassandra?

11:35.653 --> 11:38.615
I'm here for you.

11:38.697 --> 11:40.991
We all are.

11:48.707 --> 11:53.004
Percy, come on. We can make it.

11:53.087 --> 11:55.005
- [gasps]
- [Cassandra yelps]

11:58.677 --> 12:00.553
You.

12:00.636 --> 12:02.179
You did this to me.

12:02.264 --> 12:05.725
And you'll pay!

12:05.808 --> 12:08.687
[all grunting]

12:11.398 --> 12:14.609
[Orthax] The time has come.

12:14.692 --> 12:16.820
Fire the weapon.

12:19.447 --> 12:21.991
Be at peace.

12:23.159 --> 12:26.663
Wait! Please, Percy.

12:26.745 --> 12:29.707
Don't forfeit your own soul.

12:32.335 --> 12:36.465
You know who to trust, Percival.

12:38.008 --> 12:40.719
Yes. I do.

12:45.432 --> 12:47.057
♪ ♪

12:49.811 --> 12:52.272
I won't let you!

12:52.355 --> 12:53.648
[Orthax] No!

12:53.731 --> 12:55.192
[screaming]

12:56.234 --> 12:58.695
[screeching]

13:06.244 --> 13:08.163
[explosion]

13:10.331 --> 13:12.542
♪ ♪

13:12.625 --> 13:13.960
[Percy groans]

13:15.921 --> 13:20.841
Percy? Say something. Is it you?

13:20.926 --> 13:23.302
I'm afraid so.

13:23.385 --> 13:26.681
Well, most of me anyway.

13:26.764 --> 13:28.225
You shot me!

13:28.307 --> 13:30.936
Yes, well, thank you
for not dying.

13:31.019 --> 13:32.770
Yeah, you're welcome.

13:32.854 --> 13:36.566
So, that was the most fucked-up
thing I've ever seen...

13:36.649 --> 13:38.943
and I hang out with Scanlan.

13:39.027 --> 13:42.572
[Delilah laughing]

13:42.655 --> 13:44.573
How fitting.

13:44.658 --> 13:49.328
Even in your moment of triumph,
you still managed to fall short.

13:49.412 --> 13:50.871
What?

13:50.956 --> 13:55.460
You had the chance to kill me
and you failed miserably.

13:55.543 --> 13:58.171
It shouldn't surprise me,
though.

13:58.254 --> 14:00.506
You're as spineless
as your parents.

14:02.341 --> 14:05.803
Sylas is gone.
I know that suffering.

14:05.886 --> 14:09.599
Losing one's family is a wound
that cannot be mended.

14:09.682 --> 14:12.561
At least he saw the sunlight
one last time.

14:12.644 --> 14:15.563
I knew we saved
the wrong de Rolo.

14:15.647 --> 14:17.731
But it matters not.

14:17.816 --> 14:20.402
You may have stopped me today.

14:20.485 --> 14:23.779
The Whispered One
will finish what we began.

14:23.863 --> 14:27.576
And when he returns,
cities will fall,

14:27.658 --> 14:29.577
titans will rise,

14:29.661 --> 14:33.123
rivers will flow
with the blood of...

14:33.206 --> 14:34.915
[gasping]

14:35.000 --> 14:36.750
[choking, gurgling]

14:40.046 --> 14:42.006
[raspy gasping]

14:53.518 --> 14:56.395
♪ ♪

15:03.360 --> 15:04.863
I'm glad you forgave her,
brother.

15:06.530 --> 15:08.033
But I cannot.

15:14.538 --> 15:17.167
[Grog grunts]

15:17.250 --> 15:19.168
[sizzling]

15:19.251 --> 15:20.919
- Everyone ready?
- What?

15:21.004 --> 15:23.298
You mean we have to leave
this delightful place?

15:27.344 --> 15:29.471
Ah, da-da-da-da.
I don't think so, buddy.

15:29.553 --> 15:31.972
[laughs]
Regardless of its origin,

15:32.057 --> 15:33.600
it can still prove to be
an effective weapon.

15:33.682 --> 15:35.809
What? Are you forgetting
the smoke

15:35.894 --> 15:39.147
and the whole "I'm insane
with vengeance" thing?

15:39.230 --> 15:42.817
The demon is gone, Scanlan.
The curse is lifted.

15:45.653 --> 15:48.030
[sighs] Yeah,
maybe you're... Nah.

15:48.114 --> 15:49.948
[Percy] No!

15:50.033 --> 15:52.494
- [sizzling]
- You know how much that cost?

15:52.576 --> 15:55.038
How bloody long it will take me
to make ano...

15:55.120 --> 15:56.706
[screeching]

15:58.249 --> 15:59.834
Well, I'll be damned.

15:59.918 --> 16:02.796
Thank you, Scanlan.
All of you.

16:02.879 --> 16:05.631
For this second chance.

16:11.804 --> 16:14.890
Hey, how'd you know that demon
was still in there?

16:14.974 --> 16:16.475
Total guess.

16:16.558 --> 16:18.687
♪ ♪

16:18.769 --> 16:22.273
[indistinct chatter, grunting]

16:27.946 --> 16:30.280
[grunting]

16:30.365 --> 16:32.158
[man] One more on the fire then.

16:35.662 --> 16:38.748
- Thank you.
- You saved Whitestone.

16:38.831 --> 16:41.125
We're in your debt, Vox Machina.

16:41.209 --> 16:42.293
[others murmuring]

16:42.376 --> 16:44.586
W-What do we do?

16:44.671 --> 16:47.590
Just nod and smile, Kiki.

16:47.673 --> 16:50.051
Of course. Our pleasure.

16:50.134 --> 16:52.261
It was nothing, nothing at all.

16:52.345 --> 16:55.432
Huh? Oh, hello, handsome.

16:56.474 --> 16:58.475
Scanlan Shorthalt, rebel leader.

16:58.559 --> 16:59.727
Yeah, you've probably
heard of me.

16:59.811 --> 17:02.187
Anyway, I may
need a bed tonight.

17:02.272 --> 17:04.857
You see, freedom-fighting
is tiring work.

17:04.941 --> 17:07.067
So I was just wondering
if maybe... [yelps]

17:07.152 --> 17:09.738
These people just survived
the apocalypse, Scanlan.

17:09.820 --> 17:11.780
They don't need your gonorrhea.

17:11.865 --> 17:14.534
[Grog] Oh, hello,
Mr. Giant.

17:14.616 --> 17:17.036
I see you! [giggles]

17:17.119 --> 17:20.164
So, w-what happens now?

17:20.248 --> 17:22.500
Will you stay and rebuild?

17:22.584 --> 17:26.128
A de Rolo has watched
over this land for 200 years.

17:26.211 --> 17:30.340
My entire adult life has been
driven by fear and vengeance.

17:30.424 --> 17:32.926
That's not the temperament
of a leader.

17:33.010 --> 17:37.390
But you, Cass, of all our
family, you were the bravest.

17:37.473 --> 17:39.808
You are the true heir
to Whitestone.

17:39.893 --> 17:44.772
Me? But our betrayers,
they turned me.

17:44.855 --> 17:47.483
Our people will see me
as a traitor.

17:47.567 --> 17:50.194
They will see you as a survivor.

17:50.278 --> 17:54.990
Everyone here suffered from the
Briarwoods. But you endured it.

17:55.074 --> 17:57.786
We live as long
as Whitestone lives.

17:57.868 --> 18:00.954
Help me ensure it lives forever.

18:06.461 --> 18:09.297
I, uh...

18:09.380 --> 18:12.299
I meant what I said yesterday.

18:12.383 --> 18:15.178
I know, Vax.

18:15.260 --> 18:19.057
And it's the first time
anyone's ever said that to me.

18:19.140 --> 18:22.810
But we have responsibilities.

18:22.894 --> 18:25.563
To the realm. To my Aramenté.

18:25.646 --> 18:29.400
I... I just can't.

18:29.483 --> 18:31.027
I'm sorry.

18:31.109 --> 18:35.030
Oh, no. No, you're right.

18:35.114 --> 18:39.536
I, uh, um...

18:39.618 --> 18:42.622
I'm gonna walk away.

18:44.707 --> 18:46.625
[sighs]

18:46.709 --> 18:48.044
Keeper Yennen.

18:48.126 --> 18:51.588
Did any of you see a woman named
Ripley flee from the palace?

18:51.673 --> 18:54.509
Tattered clothes? Missing hand?
Total sociopath?

18:54.592 --> 18:57.135
I'm afraid not. Why?

18:57.220 --> 18:58.971
I worry we'll meet her again.

18:59.055 --> 19:01.182
Oh, hey, what about that thing
at the top of the zipper-twat?

19:01.266 --> 19:03.393
The, uh, spinning orb of death?

19:03.476 --> 19:05.936
From what you told me, it must
be connected to something

19:06.019 --> 19:07.646
beyond the veil.

19:07.730 --> 19:11.233
One of our holy men already
went to investigate it.

19:11.317 --> 19:12.986
[zapping]

19:14.778 --> 19:17.281
[screaming]

19:20.410 --> 19:21.952
Hopefully it's not dangerous.

19:22.036 --> 19:24.413
So, we stickin' around
awhile or what?

19:24.497 --> 19:26.039
I could get used
to being a hero.

19:26.124 --> 19:27.625
We need to report to Emon

19:27.709 --> 19:30.336
before Uriel's men find us
and drag us back.

19:30.420 --> 19:33.088
Really, brother?
We could just...

19:33.172 --> 19:37.009
Run? [laughs softly]
I think we're done with that.

19:37.093 --> 19:41.346
Besides, you need to get punched
in the face now and then...

19:41.431 --> 19:42.807
to know you're alive.

19:44.558 --> 19:47.019
Right. I'll find us some horses.

19:47.103 --> 19:49.564
[Keyleth] Oh, uh, actually...

19:49.646 --> 19:52.733
I might be able to get us home
a little quicker.

19:52.817 --> 19:55.068
Oh, what'd you have in mind,
green?

19:55.153 --> 19:57.404
Well, there's this tree spell.

19:57.488 --> 20:00.032
But, well, it only works
on trees I've seen before,

20:00.115 --> 20:01.701
and they have to be alive,

20:01.784 --> 20:03.577
and also I have to be
strong enough,

20:03.661 --> 20:05.329
and I think I can only do it,
like, once a day,

20:05.413 --> 20:08.499
so, you know what,
just forget I brought it up.

20:08.583 --> 20:11.794
Darling. You've got this.

20:14.881 --> 20:19.426
Right. Yeah. Uh, totally.

20:19.509 --> 20:21.220
Thanks, Vex.

20:25.724 --> 20:27.769
Sun Tree.

20:27.852 --> 20:29.979
Talk to me.

20:30.063 --> 20:32.065
♪ ♪

20:38.320 --> 20:40.323
♪ ♪

20:47.829 --> 20:51.209
[laughs softly]
Aren't trees just the best?

20:55.587 --> 20:58.215
♪ ♪

20:58.298 --> 21:00.593
Whoa. I think I peed a little.

21:00.676 --> 21:03.136
- Sure did, buddy.
- [Keyleth] Uh, guys?

21:03.221 --> 21:05.932
I kinda can't hold this
for too long.

21:06.015 --> 21:08.101
Right, everybody in!

21:08.183 --> 21:10.185
[Grog laughing]

21:10.269 --> 21:11.770
[grunts, laughs]

21:11.854 --> 21:13.355
[laughs softly]

21:19.237 --> 21:21.239
[magical chiming]

21:21.321 --> 21:23.115
[birds chirping]

21:23.199 --> 21:25.242
♪ ♪

21:31.499 --> 21:33.500
[metal clinking]

21:39.132 --> 21:41.342
[snoring]

21:43.510 --> 21:47.682
Ow! [groans]
I hate doors.

21:47.765 --> 21:49.182
I gotcha, buddies.

21:53.438 --> 21:55.355
Aw, thanks, Pikey!

21:55.440 --> 21:57.316
[squeals, laughs]

21:57.400 --> 22:01.319
[grunts] Okay.
I can't really breathe so...

22:01.403 --> 22:03.030
- [snoring]
- Ha ha!

22:03.114 --> 22:05.657
My masterpiece is complete!

22:05.741 --> 22:07.535
The epic story of our adventure.

22:07.617 --> 22:11.288
The dragon, the vampires,
the cyclops I vanquished.

22:11.372 --> 22:12.582
What cyclops?

22:12.664 --> 22:14.333
Oh, I may have taken
some artistic license.

22:14.416 --> 22:16.335
[chuckles]
Wonderful, Scanlan.

22:16.419 --> 22:17.961
Looking forward to reading it.

22:18.046 --> 22:21.883
[scoffs] Read it? This tale is
far too great for a lousy book.

22:21.965 --> 22:23.968
No, our legend shall be told...

22:24.051 --> 22:26.554
♪ In song ♪

22:26.636 --> 22:28.138
[all groaning]

22:28.221 --> 22:29.473
- Yes!
- [groans]

22:29.557 --> 22:31.308
♪ Sit down, my friends ♪

22:31.392 --> 22:33.478
♪ And I'll start rockin' ya ♪

22:33.560 --> 22:35.813
♪ With the epic legend of... ♪

22:35.896 --> 22:37.647
- [record scratches]
- [Jarett] Vox Machina!

22:37.731 --> 22:41.068
[Vax] Excellent timing, Jarett.

22:42.444 --> 22:45.615
The Sovereign has summoned you
to the Cloudtop.

22:45.698 --> 22:48.076
What? Like, now?

22:50.368 --> 22:53.122
♪ ♪

22:58.376 --> 23:01.923
[quiet chatter]

23:03.007 --> 23:05.593
Vax'ildan! [laughs]

23:05.675 --> 23:08.930
Glad to see you alive
and with all your...

23:09.012 --> 23:11.265
extremities intact.

23:11.348 --> 23:14.727
Looking sharp, Gilmore,
as always.

23:14.810 --> 23:17.145
Oh, this old thing?

23:19.106 --> 23:21.192
Any idea what
all this fuss is about?

23:21.275 --> 23:25.195
The criers said Sovereign Uriel
is to make a proclamation.

23:25.278 --> 23:29.407
Seems juicy;
the whole council showed up.

23:29.491 --> 23:31.743
Friends. In recent weeks,

23:31.827 --> 23:34.454
Tal'Dorei has been
beset by evil,

23:34.538 --> 23:37.583
wearing the faces
of monsters and men.

23:37.666 --> 23:40.877
I relied on my best judgment
to meet these threats.

23:40.961 --> 23:44.339
But sadly, that judgment
was greatly corrupted.

23:44.423 --> 23:48.552
The truth is, I allowed
strangers into our midst,

23:48.635 --> 23:51.972
entrusting them with power
they never should have had.

23:52.056 --> 23:54.642
- Vox Machina...
- [gasping]

23:54.724 --> 23:56.144
saved us from this threat...

23:56.227 --> 23:57.686
- [relieved sighs]
- yet again.

23:59.146 --> 24:01.398
They showed me that
the wisdom of a group,

24:01.481 --> 24:03.526
no matter how unconventional,

24:03.608 --> 24:05.819
outweighs that
of the individual.

24:05.903 --> 24:08.739
There is foresight
in friendship.

24:08.823 --> 24:11.826
My weakness put the realm
in jeopardy.

24:11.909 --> 24:13.286
But never again.

24:15.829 --> 24:17.914
And so, with humility,

24:17.999 --> 24:21.169
I hereby renounce the throne
and cede the government

24:21.251 --> 24:22.711
to the Council of Tal'Dorei.

24:22.795 --> 24:25.714
[gasping, murmuring]

24:25.798 --> 24:29.050
These wise patriots shall ensure

24:29.134 --> 24:31.929
- that Emon stands forever.
- [cheering]

24:32.012 --> 24:35.266
Now, in addition to the council
members you already know,

24:35.348 --> 24:37.351
- we will be adding a few more.
- [high-pitched ringing]

24:37.434 --> 24:39.311
- [groaning]
- Vex, are you all right?

24:39.394 --> 24:42.064
Specifically, pillars of the
community who have held up...

24:42.147 --> 24:45.442
[bell tolling]

24:45.526 --> 24:47.528
♪ ♪

24:51.115 --> 24:53.075
Gods above us...

24:53.159 --> 24:56.077
[panicked chatter]

24:56.162 --> 24:59.039
♪ ♪

24:59.123 --> 25:01.125
[gasps] No.

25:06.923 --> 25:08.924
[hissing]

25:12.470 --> 25:13.887
[roars]

25:13.971 --> 25:16.265
[roaring loudly]

25:18.267 --> 25:20.269
♪ ♪

26:05.272 --> 26:07.275
Chirp.
